                            <comment id="12770291" author="phunt" created="Mon, 26 Oct 2009 23:35:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;send_ping is calling wake_io_thread itself, so this is a particularly bad situation (forces a tight loop)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;solution is to update last_send as last_send_attempt when attempting to send, whether successful or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12770292" author="phunt" created="Mon, 26 Oct 2009 23:36:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigning to Ben. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should verify that something like this can&apos;t happen in the java either. From my looking&lt;br/&gt;
it seems not, but would be good to have addl verification.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12770394" author="breed" created="Tue, 27 Oct 2009 05:34:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this patch fixes the problem by only sending a ping if there isn&apos;t something already queued. the test checks for clients sending gratuitous pings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
